# JPA / Hibernate

Aligned with Spring Boot 4.0.x / Hibernate ORM 7.0.x / Jakarta JPA 3.2.

## Entity Design

### Field Access
- Prefer field-based access (annotations on fields, not getters)
- Hibernate proxies work with field access; getter-based access requires careful proxy handling

### Identity and Equality
```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "orders")
@Getter @Setter
public class Order {
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    @Column(nullable = false, unique = true, length = 36)
    private String orderNumber;

    @Version
    private Long version;

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) {
        if (this == o) return true;
        if (!(o instanceof Order other)) return false;
        return orderNumber != null && orderNumber.equals(other.orderNumber);
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return Objects.hash(orderNumber);
    }
}
```
- **ALWAYS** implement `equals`/`hashCode` on a natural/business key, not `@Id` alone
- `@Id`-based equality breaks for new (transient) entities before `persist()`
- Use `instanceof` (not `getClass()`) to support Hibernate proxies

### Optimistic Locking
- **ALWAYS** add `@Version` to entities modified concurrently
- Handle `OptimisticLockException` with a retry or user notification

### Lombok on Entities
- `@Getter` / `@Setter` -- allowed on entities
- **NEVER** `@Data` -- generates `equals`/`hashCode` using all fields including lazy collections
- **NEVER** `@ToString` with lazy associations -- triggers unintended loading
- `@Builder` -- avoid on entities; use for DTOs only

## Relationship Mapping

### Conventions
| Relationship | Owner Side | Inverse Side | Default Fetch |
|-------------|-----------|--------------|---------------|
| `@ManyToOne` | The "many" side (FK column) | -- | `EAGER` (override to `LAZY`) |
| `@OneToMany` | -- | `mappedBy` | `LAZY` |
| `@ManyToMany` | Either side (pick one) | `mappedBy` | `LAZY` |
| `@OneToOne` | FK holder | `mappedBy` | `EAGER` (override to `LAZY`) |

### Bidirectional Helper Methods
```java
@Entity
public class Order {
    @OneToMany(mappedBy = "order", cascade = CascadeType.ALL, orphanRemoval = true)
    private List<OrderItem> items = new ArrayList<>();

    public void addItem(OrderItem item) {
        items.add(item);
        item.setOrder(this);
    }

    public void removeItem(OrderItem item) {
        items.remove(item);
        item.setOrder(null);
    }
}
```

### CascadeType Rules
| Cascade | Use When |
|---------|----------|
| `CascadeType.ALL` + `orphanRemoval = true` | Parent owns children exclusively (Order -> OrderItems) |
| `CascadeType.PERSIST`, `MERGE` | Parent creates/updates children but doesn't delete independently |
| **NONE** (default) | Independent lifecycle (Order -> Customer) |

**NEVER** cascade from child to parent or across aggregate boundaries.

## Fetch Strategies

### Default: LAZY Everything
```java
@ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY) // override EAGER default
private Customer customer;

@OneToMany(mappedBy = "order", fetch = FetchType.LAZY) // already default
private List<OrderItem> items;
```

### Loading Strategies
| Strategy | When to Use |
|----------|------------|
| **JOIN FETCH** (JPQL) | Known query, specific use case |
| **`@EntityGraph`** | Declarative, reusable across queries |
| **`@BatchSize`** | Collection loaded in loop (reduces N+1 to N/batch) |
| **DTO Projection** | Read-only views (best performance) |

## Repository Conventions

```java
public interface OrderRepository extends JpaRepository<Order, Long>,
    JpaSpecificationExecutor<Order> {

    // Derived query
    List<Order> findByStatusAndCustomerId(OrderStatus status, Long customerId);

    // JPQL with JOIN FETCH
    @Query("SELECT o FROM Order o JOIN FETCH o.items WHERE o.id = :id")
    Optional<Order> findByIdWithItems(@Param("id") Long id);

    // Modifying query (bulk update)
    @Modifying
    @Query("UPDATE Order o SET o.status = :status WHERE o.id IN :ids")
    int updateStatusByIds(@Param("status") OrderStatus status, @Param("ids") List<Long> ids);

    // Native query
    @Query(value = "SELECT * FROM orders WHERE created_at > :since", nativeQuery = true)
    List<Order> findRecentOrders(@Param("since") Instant since);
}
```

- One repository per aggregate root
- `JpaRepository` for full CRUD + paging
- `JpaSpecificationExecutor` for dynamic queries
- `@Modifying` with `clearAutomatically = true` if subsequent reads in same transaction

## Transactions

- `@Transactional` on **service methods**, never on repositories
- `@Transactional(readOnly = true)` at class level for read-heavy services; override with `@Transactional` on write methods
- Keep transactions short; do not hold across remote calls
- `Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW` for audit logs that must survive rollback

## Hibernate Configuration

```yaml
spring:
  jpa:
    open-in-view: false          # ALWAYS disable in production
    hibernate:
      ddl-auto: validate         # production: validate; dev: update; CI: create-drop
    properties:
      hibernate:
        default_batch_fetch_size: 25
        jdbc:
          batch_size: 50
        order_inserts: true
        order_updates: true
        generate_statistics: false # enable temporarily for debugging
    show-sql: false               # use logging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=DEBUG instead
```

### Naming Strategy
Spring Boot defaults to `SpringPhysicalNamingStrategy` (camelCase -> snake_case). Keep this default.

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Problem | Fix |
|-------------|---------|-----|
| `FetchType.EAGER` on any association | Loads entire object graph | Default to `LAZY`; fetch explicitly |
| `@Data` on entities | Broken `equals`/`hashCode`, lazy loading issues | `@Getter`/`@Setter` + manual `equals`/`hashCode` |
| `spring.jpa.open-in-view: true` | Lazy loading in controllers, N+1 in views | Disable; use JOIN FETCH or DTOs |
| Exposing entities in API responses | Tight coupling, security risk, lazy loading errors | Use record DTOs + MapStruct |
| Business logic in repositories | Hard to test, violates SRP | Keep in service layer |
| `ddl-auto: update` in production | Uncontrolled schema changes | Use Flyway; set `validate` |
| No `@Version` on mutable entities | Lost updates under concurrency | Add `@Version` field |
| `CascadeType.ALL` across aggregates | Unintended deletes across boundaries | Cascade within aggregate only |

